<h2>How it works</h2>

<p>Change the value of the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/display">display property</a> with the provided responsive display utility classes. A subset of all possible values was carefully selected. Classes can be combined for various effects as you need.</p>

<h2>Notation</h2>

<p>Display utility classes that apply to utility breakpoints. As such, the classes are named using the format:</p>

<ul>
  <li><code>.d-{value}</code> for <code>xs</code></li>
  <li><code>.d-{value}@{breakpoint}</code> for <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code>, and <code>lg</code>.</li>
</ul>

Where <em>value</em> is one of:

<ul>
  <li><code>none</code></li>
  <li><code>inline</code></li>
  <li><code>inline-block</code></li>
  <li><code>block</code></li>
  <li><code>flex</code></li>
  <li><code>inline-flex</code></li>
  <li><code>grid</code></li>
</ul>

<p>Like every other utility class display values can be altered by changing the <code>utilities.$custom</code> variable and recompiling the SCSS.</p>

<p>The media queries affect screen widths with the given breakpoint or larger. For example, <code>.d-none@md</code> sets <code>display: none;</code> on both <code>md</code> and <code>lg</code> screens.</p>

<h2>Example</h2>

{% snippet %}
<div class="d-inline d-block@md p-s bg-primary text-white">Inline on mobile</div>
<div class="d-inline d-block@md p-s bg-black text-white">Inline on mobile</div>
{% endsnippet %}

<h2>Hiding elements</h2>

<p>You may want to hide elements responsively for each screen size instead of creating a second view. Responsive display classes help fasten mobile-friendly development, in particular for showing and hiding elements by device.</p>

<p>To hide elements simply use the <code>.d-none</code> class or one of the <code>.d-none@{sm,md,lg}</code> classes for any responsive screen variation.</p>

<p>To show an element only on a given interval of screen sizes you can combine one <code>.d-none@*</code> class with a <code>.d-*@*</code> class, for example <code>.d-none .d-block@md .d-none@lg</code></p>
